My situation is quite similar. I need to build a new website and am currently organizing my requirements regarding accessibility and privacy (so no tools like Google Analytics), and researching how to use Signal for video calls; this requires a lot of customer education! But I think it's worth it.
@user4 @user3 You can definitely do it! I'm happy to share my experience with you.
Website: you can check out @user5. It looks very user-friendly, has a nice interface, and is open source. I plan to migrate one of my websites to it before my next renewal.
Signal: check out cal.com. It's an open source calendar service that integrates scheduling video calls with Element, JITSI, and others. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested yet whether it's only for messaging or also for video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encryption, decentralized, open source.
